            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1040" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1040">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6463/9–2645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-26">September 26,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1559. Departure following personnel Shanghai Power Company whose presence
                    Shanghai urgently desired by Army authorities being delayed pending receipt of
                    authority from Chinese FonOff to issue visas: Charles J. Ferguson, John K.
                    Rummel, Kenneth R. MacKinnon and Carl R. Weidinger, all Americans, and Francis
                    M. Young and Stephen E. Clark, both British.</p>
                <p>Please bring this matter to attention of FonOff, pointing out urgent need of
                    services these personnel in restoration power and light facilities Shanghai and
                    requesting issuance visas be expedited.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
